`Gdx.input` is just a `public static` field on the `Gdx` class. You can initialize it to anything that implements the `Input` interface. 

This means you can create your own class that implements `Input` and is aware of the `Robot` so that it can query the robot for the key-press status, for example:

	public class RobotInput implements Input {

		private Robot robot;

		public RobotInput(Robot robot) {
			this.robot = robot;
		}

		/* loads of other methods from the Input interface omitted for brevity */

		@Override
		public boolean isKeyPressed(int key) {
			return robot.isKeyPressed(key);
		}
	}

Then you can initialize `Gdx.input` like:

	Robot robot = new Robot();
	Gdx.input = new RobotInput(robot);

	robot.keyPress(Input.Keys.LEFT);
	if(Gdx.input.isKeyPressed(Input.Keys.LEFT)) {
		x -= 5;
	}

