This method creates a new `outputArray` of length to the input array and two integer `pos` and `product`.\
In the first for loop the total product of the array is found then in the next loop the variable `pos` is increased by 1, just to get the index number of the outputArray. Then using the variable pos the outputArray gets filled by dividing the total product of the array with each element of the inputArray which results in what you&#39;re looking for.\
This might throw an Exception when the product is more than the maximum value that any Integer can hold.

     public static int[] calculateProduct(int[] array)
     {
         int[] outputArray = new int[array.length];
         int pos = -1;
         int product = 1;
        
         for(int a : array)
         {
             product *= a;
         }
        
         for(int x : array)
         {
             pos++;
             outputArray[pos] = product / x;
         }
        
         return outputArray;
     }

